steps.instruction:
For a more step by step-by-step guide go [here](https://www.kingarthurflour.com/blog/2016/08/28/make-absolute-favorite-brownie)

1. Preheat oven to 350F
2. Lightly grease a 9" x 13" pan
3. Combine the melted butter and sugar, stirring until smooth
4. Stir in the cocoa, salt, baking powder, vanilla, and espresso powder
5. Beat in the eggs one at a time
6. Scrape the bowl, then add the water, stirring until smooth
7. Add the flour, nuts, and chips, stirring until thoroughly combined
8. Spoon the batter into the prepared pan
9. Bake the brownies for 28 to 30 minutes, until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean, or with a few moist crumbs attached
    - The brownies should feel set both on the edges and in the center
10. Remove the brownies from the oven, and cool them on a rack before cutting and serving. Glaze or frost, if desired


#### Tips
- Be sure to let the brownies cool before you cut and serve them. When they first come out of the oven they'll be like chocolate cake; but as they cool they settle, and "cake" becomes "dense cake" — the perfect cake-type brownie

ingredients.note: Optional; can swap with an equal amount of pecans
